# MuseDAM globals.css Enforcement (Highest Priority)

## Trigger Conditions

- Mention of globals.css, color, theme, Dark Mode, primary, background, border.
- New project/component when globals.css missing or incorrect.
- Any reskin or design restoration.

## Token Gap Policy

- `globals.css` is the source of truth for project tokens. If Figma introduces a new color, typography, spacing, radius, or shadow token that cannot be represented by the current variables, list the gap first instead of inventing one-off values in TSX.
- Only extend tokens intentionally. Do not patch missing design values with hard-coded classes or inline styles just to finish a screen.

## Forced Content (overwrite completely – no old Ant colors allowed)

